{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6a740c93-6e50-4de8-abaa-ff755b1192e3","content":"Here's my analysis of the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n## 1. Deep Import Chain (High Impact)\n\nThe project imports `level1.props`, which imports `level2.props`, which imports `level3.props`. Each nested import requires MSBuild to locate, open, parse, and evaluate another file during the **evaluation phase**. Deep chains multiply disk I/O and XML parsing overhead before any build targets run. Flatten these into fewer files or a single `.props` where possible.\n\n## 2. Overly Broad Glob Pattern (High Impact)\n\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n\nThe `**\\*.*` glob recursively scans *every* file in the project tree during evaluation. It only excludes `bin/` and `obj/`, meaning it will enumerate `.git/`, `node_modules/`, and any other large directory. Use `DefaultItemExcludes` or restrict the glob to specific subdirectories/extensions:\n\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"src\\**\\*.cs\" />\n```\n\n## 3. File I/O via Property Function During Evaluation (Medium Impact)\n\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n\nThis calls `File.ReadAllText` at **evaluation time** — before any target executes. MSBuild evaluation should be fast and side-effect-free; synchronous file reads block the evaluator. Move this to a target that runs during the **execution phase** instead:\n\n```xml\n<Target Name=\"ReadBuildNotes\" BeforeTargets=\"Build\">\n  <ReadLinesFromFile File=\"build-notes.txt\">\n    <Output TaskParameter=\"Lines\" ItemName=\"BuildNotesLines\"/>\n  </ReadLinesFromFile>\n</Target>\n```\n\n## Evaluation vs. Execution Phase\n\nMSBuild processes a project in two phases:\n- **Evaluation** – parses XML, resolves imports, expands properties/items, evaluates globs. This happens for *every* design-time load (IDE, restore, etc.).\n- **Execution** – runs targets and tasks.\n\nAll three issues above add cost to evaluation, which is invoked far more frequently than a full build. Keeping evaluation lightweight is critical for IDE responsiveness and restore performance.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cf5dc5e4-fb41-4aec-b17a-ddeb688f146c","outputTokens":557,"requestId":"5C09:282C31:1DC6CF4:21A5CB7:6A07CA29"},"id":"496e653a-cb07-42a9-a355-0c2861317043","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:36:54.369Z","parentId":"702a9ee5-77c8-456e-8054-61de040ed1a4"}
